sentences: Saha was born on November 1, 1991 in Bangladesh.
In 2011, Saha started producing electronic music under the moniker No Pets Allowed.
In February 2014, Saha decided to part ways with the project and begin what is now known as Jai Wolf.
In late 2014, Skrillex turned Jai Wolf's bootleg remix of "Ease My Mind" into an official remix.
In 2015, Jai Wolf released his debut single "Indian Summer" through ODESZA's label, Foreign Family Collective.
The track also earned a spot on the Triple J 2015 Hottest 100 in Australia.
In May 2016, Jai Wolf released his follow up single, "Drive", through Foreign Family Collective.
On November 18, 2016, Jai Wolf released his debut EP, Kindred Spirits, through Mom + Pop music.
In April 2017, Jai Wolf released his single, "Starlight" which featured Mr Gabriel, followed by a performance at the 2017 Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival.

On January 14, 2019, Jai Wolf announced his debut album, The Cure to Loneliness, being released on April 5, 2019.
